          "timestamp": "2026-03-27T04:04:19.687Z",
          "id": "dd2eb33f-f4e2-482f-b3bc-0345af96cfd2"
        },
        {
          "type": "assistant",
          "text": "Clean. The `change_history` line ranges will now serialize like this:\n\n```json\n\"files\": {\n  \"arithmetic_ops.py\": {\n    \"added_lines\": [\"4\", \"6\", \"8-9\", \"11-16\"],\n    \"deleted_lines\": [\"4\", \"6\", \"8-10\", \"12-14\"]\n  }\n}\n```\n\nInstead of the previous nested array form `[[4,4],[6,6],[8,9],[11,16]]`. Single-line ranges like `(4, 4)` become `\"4\"`, and multi-line ranges like `(8, 9)` become `\"8-9\"` — matching exactly how the attestation header section formats them. The helper `format_line_range_tuple` mirrors the `LineRange::Single` / `LineRange::Range` arms in the existing `format_line_ranges` function.",
